Beeminder
=========

[Beeminder](https://www.beeminder.com) is an online service for goal tracking. Integrating it with GitHub allows you to automatically add a datapoint to a Beeminder goal when you push a commit to a GitHub repository.

Install Notes
-------------

1. [Signup](https://www.beeminder.com/users/sign_up) for a Beeminder account (you can sign in with GitHub)
2. **username** - Use your Beeminder username
3. **goal_slug** - How your goal appears in the url (eg. if user "alice" has a goal "foo", foo's url will be "http://www.beeminder.com/*alice*/goals/*foo*". Where "foo" is the goal's slug.)
4. You can find your **auth_token** at https://www.beeminder.com/api/v1/auth_token.json
